result.execSummary:
The defendant Tyler D Hansen was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Narcotic Drugs, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(am).
  • Possession of Narcotic Drugs, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(am).
  • Possession of Narcotic Drugs, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(am).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. case called at 10:03am. [MK]
Defendant Tyler D Hansen in court with Attorney Michael C. Witt.  ADA Theresa Beck appears for the State of Wisconsin.
Today's hearing is scheduled on the State's Motion to Amend Bond. 
The Court discloses to the parties that a personal contact that was received related to the case.  Judge Weston indicates that she received a telephone call from her stepmother with a question about the procedure for requesting open records. Judge Weston's stepmother and her stepmother's current husband both work for Lutheran Social Services; request; she works for LSS as well as her current husband;  apparantly LSS contracted with Mr. Hansen.  The Court would recuse if the parties request. 
Counsel each indicate they have not objection to this Court proceeding on the case. 
The Court informs the parties that this case will transfer, by Judicial Rotation, to Branch III on January 1st. 
Arguments given on the bond-motion. 

The Court grants the State's Motion to Amend Bond, but creates exceptions so that the conditions of the $10,000.00 signature bond are now: 
-Not to possess or use drugs or controlled substances without a valid prescription
-No possession of drug paraphernalia without a valid prescription 
-Not to possess any prescriptions belonging to any other person
--Mr. Hansen may not be present at or enter any Abilities properties with the exceptions that:  Mr. Hansen may be present at 426 McMillen Street and may enter that premise; Mr. Hansen may be present at, but may not enter the following properties:  503 Nikki Lane in Fort Atkinson WI, 1122 Green Street in Fort Atkinson, and 117-119 Healy Lane in Fort Atkinson.

The Court and counsel discuss rescheduling of the Preliminary Hearing date. 
recess 10:21am.
